}
}

\subtree{
\title{Conclusion}
\p{\strong{Protocol ACSet} enables:}

\ul{
\li{✅ \strong{Formal composition} of protocols without ad-hoc integration}
\li{✅ \strong{Verification} that protocols can safely interoperate}
\li{✅ \strong{Evolution narratives} showing protocol families over time}
\li{✅ \strong{Optimal stacking} guided by categorical mathematics}
\li{✅ \strong{Data sovereignty} through principled system design}
}

\p{Rather than asking "which protocol should I use?", ask "what properties do I need, and how do I compose protocols to achieve them?"}
}

